
<html>
    <head>
        {% block stylesheets %}
            {{ encore_entry_link_tags('app') }}
            {{ encore_entry_link_tags('offert-form') }}
            {{ encore_entry_link_tags('home') }}
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.2/css/all.min.css">
            <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Brawler&family=Indie+Flower&family=Life+Savers&family=Short+Stack&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
        {% endblock %}
        {% block javascripts %}
            {{ encore_entry_script_tags('app') }}
            {{ encore_entry_script_tags('skills_js') }}
        {% endblock %}
    </head>
    {% block body%}
        <div class="offert-details">
            <h1>Event</h1>
            <p class="date">
                <i class="far fa-calendar-check"></i>22.03.2022 <br>
                <i class="far fa-clock"></i>5 p.m.</p>
            <p>
                It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when
                looking at its layout.
                The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal distribution of letters,
                as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like readable English.
                Many desktop publishing packages and web page
                editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for 'lorem ipsum' will
                uncover many web sites still in their infancy. Various versions have evolved over the years,
                sometimes by accident, sometimes on purpose (injected humour and the like).


            </p>

            <div class="must-haves">
                <h2>Must have:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your own microphones</li>
                    <li>Guitarist & pianist</li>
                    <li> English language</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>
        <div class="form-container">
            <div class="artist-form">
                <h1 id="try"> Let's try and apply!</h1>
                <p>Here are some tips to follow:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Be concrete</li>
                    <li>Give conditions on which you are prepared</li>
                    <li>Be ready to perform </li>
                    <li>Have fun!</li>
                </ul>
                <img src="../../assets/img/guitarist.png" alt="">
                {{ form_start(offertForm) }}
                    {{ form_widget(offertForm) }}
                <b-button type="submit">Submit</b-button>
                {{ form_end(offertForm) }}

            </div>
            <div class="show-skills">
                <h1 v-if="skillsArray.length>0 ">Skills:</h1>
                <div v-if="skillsArray.length<=10" class="allSkills">
                    <div  class="skill"  v-for="skill in skillsArray" :key="skills"  >
                        <button v-on:click="removeElement(skill)">X</button>
                        {{ "{{ skill }}" }}
                    </div>
                    <p v-if="skillsArray.length>=10"> Only 10 skills allowed</p>
                </div>

            </div>
            <div class="show-requirements">
                <h1 v-if="requirementsArray.length>0 ">Requirements:</h1>
                <div v-if="requirementsArray.length<=10" class="allSkills">
                    <div  class="skill"  v-for="requirement in requirementsArray" :key="requirements"  >
                        <button v-on:click="removeElement(requirement)">X</button>
                        {{ "{{ requirement }}" }}
                    </div>
                    <p v-if="requirementsArray.length>=10"> Only 10 skills allowed</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="applicants">
            <h1>Those who already applied:</h1>
            <ul>
                <li>Ola</li>
                <li>Kasia</li>
                <li>Krzy≈õ</li>
                <li>Emil</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    {%  endblock  %}
</html>